Text: I wanted to bring some friends along to wish you a happy birthday. We have we have Lee Kuan Yew whose memoirs We both had to read because he kept suing everyone.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: We had mr. Kaczynski who led to the purchase of the wax bust of Lenin.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: We had Mr. Jamil who was kind enough to visit in London, but nonetheless led with the purchase some good Polish vodka the House of Lords.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: We had Mr. Gutnick, another frenemy, who was insistent upon us going to Victoria.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: And we had Mr Gopal, a judge, Gopel Swee Ram, who brought us all to Malaysia.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: But in a time of COVID and lockdown, I just wanted to remind you of all the things we've been able to do around the world.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: And as always to thank you, because at Dow Jones, at the Wall Street Journal. Knowing that you were there to defend us made us both braver and better.
Speaker: Stuart

Text: So I hope you have a great birthday and I hope soon enough we can end up being in the same place and have a glass to toast it. Take care.
Speaker: Stuart
